What happens after I submit on the form?
a) On the form, on the submit, we add an eventListener == .when this even happens, we prevent the default action
      var form = document.querySelector("#movie-search-form")
      form.addEventListener("submit",formSubmitted)

      function formSubmitted(event) {
        event.preventDefault();
        var query = document.querSelector("#query");
        var url = http:"//www.omdbapi.com/?s=" + query.value;

        $.get(url,movieResults);
        }

        function movieResults(results){
          var movieArray = results.Search;
          //for each item in the array,you will place that ONE item into the displayMovie function
          movieArray.forEach(displayMovie);
        }


b) In order to Search the omdb database, we need to access it with a url
c) Create the URL by concantenating the api URL + whatever is value in the input field
d) Makes a request to omdb for info (ajac call and JSON results are returned)

Review of callBack function that you have seen
a) $.get(url, callBackfunction)
.e.g. $.get(url,movieResults)
Using $.get jquery function, you "get" the data from the URL and place the data into the next function to run)

b) form.addEventListener(formSubmitted)
"Add an event listener" on the form, on "submit" of this form, do the next function ("formSubmitted")

c) On any array, do something
array.forEach(dosomething)
For each item in the array, take one of those items and do something

displayEachMovie
a) Create 4 elements (li, div div, a)
      function displayMovie(movie){
        var item = document.createElement("li");
        var movie = document.createElement("div");
        var link = document.createElement("a");
        var release = document.createElement("div");
      }
b) set Attributes to all of those elements (class="movie",href=url)
set text Content to show TITLE and RELEASE NOTE on my DOM
      var name = movie["Title"];
      movie.textContent = name;

      var year = movie["Year"]
      release.textContent = year;
c) set Attributes such classes, href, target on my newly created elements
      item.setAttribute("class","movie");
      movie.setAttribute("class", "movie-title");
      release.setAttribute("class","movie-release-date");

      var url = "http://www.imdbcom/title/" + movie[imdbID]
      link.setAttribute("href",urlIMDB);
      linke.setAttribute("target","_blank");
d) append it to the appropriate parent for it to show up on the DOM
